dismissalText.commentary: Shahriar Nafees c & b Smith 56 (73b 6x4 0x6 106m) SR: 76.71

dismissalComment.html: that's a soft and silly shot from Nafees and it's undone the only bit of good cricket Bangladesh has played today. Smith flighted the ball and drew Nafees into the drive again. He ended up chipping it straight back to the bowler. One of the easier caught and bowled chances that was.

stunningly caught at first slip! The ball was pretty ordinary, on a length wide outside off, Tamim went after it, driving with power. He didn't make proper contact though and the thick outside edge flew at furious pace towards the left of Watson's head at first slip. Watson moved quickly, taking the catch with both hands. Made it look much simpler than it was.

Bangladesh needed Kayes to kick on and anchor the innings after his excruciatingly slow start. He's gone now, after playing a rash shot. A new batsman will have to come in and get set all over again.

batsmen.shot: off side drive on front foot

commentTextItems.html: Ponting has his moment in Watson's sun, pulling the ball through backward square to score the winning runs. Bangladesh's torment is over.

commentPostTextItems.html: Watson also scored the most runs in boundaries in an ODI innings. The previous record was Herschelle Gibbs's 126 runs in boundaries during his 175 in Johannesburg in 2006.

Watson scored 185 off 96 balls, out of a total of 232. 80% of the runs. "Made my job easy," Ponting tells Neo Sports. "Just had to get a single to give him strike. No one expected it to get over that fast. I have been lucky to play with some great players, Watto has played some great innings ... this was an amazing innings. Some of those sixes would have cleared any boundary in the world. Probably won't sink into us for a while how good that was ..."
This is also the highest score by an Australian in an ODI. Beating Hayden's 181 against New Zealand.

Shakib looks a little shell shocked at the presentation ceremony. "He batted really well, all the credit goes to him ... We put on a reasonable total, but the way he batted ... when we started with spinners the ball was coming on to the bat nicely, by the time the ball stopped coming on to the bat he was well set and hitting everything."
Clarke: "That's probably the best innings I've seen. Hit the ball so cleanly from the start today ... full credit to Watto." Clarke's also happy with the way his spinners bowled.

Shane Watson is the Man of the Match. Obviously. "Nice day today," he says with a smile. "Everything came off and a little bit of luck as well." Was the sixes record planned? "I had no idea, I was pretty tired and didn't want to run too much. Was pretty hot and humid so I tried to limit my running and it worked out nicely. The ball didn't turn too much today ... made it easier to execute."

That's it from us at ESPNcricinfo for the moment, join us day after tomorrow for the final game of this series. Did I mention that Australia have won it 2-0? I'm off to watch happy animated movies after this violence. Thank you for all your emails today. Cheers.

commentTextItems.html: mis-hit through midwicket for a single

commentPostTextItems.html: Come on Ponting, leave the winning runs to Watto.

commentTextItems.html: well he's got his 15th!! This time with a cool swing through the line, lofting the ball straight over the fielder on the long-on boundary
full toss on middle and leg stump, Watson fails to hit his 15th, managing to swing it through square leg for a measly four.
full ball outside off, Watson chops own on it and plays towards point
Ponting drives straight down the ground for a single

yawn. Watson gets down on one knee, swings his bat with the power of a superhuman, and hits his 14th six, over midwicket again, with a slog sweep. This is getting stale now. How about a reverse-sweep for six?

commentTextItems.html: Watson aims for another leg-side boundary and misses
it's a disappointing four. Watson pulls with power into the gap between two people on the midwicket boundary

commentPreTextItems.html: Well had Bangladesh scored a few more runs, I have no doubt that Watson would have gone past 200 today. He is unstoppable.

commentTextItems.html: Watson pulls and misses this time. Getting beaten outside off stump
and he's broken it. His 13th six. Again heaved over wide long-on. He takes the record for most sixes in an innings from Xavier Marshall. Bangladesh want this over with now

commentPreTextItems.html: I'm getting so many angry emails directed at Oscar Wood from Sachin fans.

commentTextItems.html: Watson equals the world record for most sixes in an innings by heaving the ball over long-on. That's his 12th and he draws level with Xavier Marshall.
a low full toss and Watson drives to long-off to keep strike

headshotImage.caption: Ricky Ponting player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ricky Ponting player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: a yorker, and for once Watson has no option but to defend
driven fluently off the front foot through cover, Ponting letting Watson do all the hard work!
Watson plonks that heavy foot forward and drills the ball down the ground to long off
Watson aims for down the ground and unbelievably it doesn't come off. He slices it in the air over point to bring up his 150

commentPreTextItems.html: Xavier Marshall holds the record for most sixes in an ODI innings - 12 v Canada. Watson has 11.

commentTextItems.html: driven off the front foot through cover

commentPostTextItems.html: "I wish Australia were chasing 400, then Watson could get 300, take that Sachin," says Oscar Wood.

commentTextItems.html: Gulp. Watson sees a short ball, and pulls again, giving it plenty of air time as it makes the journey from pitch to stand beyond wide long-on

dismissalText.long: c Mahmudullah b Shakib Al Hasan
dismissalText.commentary: Brad Haddin c Mahmudullah b Shakib Al Hasan 8 (19b 1x4 0x6 28m) SR: 42.1

dismissalComment.html: caught at midwicket. It's Robin, though, not Batman. Haddin charges and tries to hit over the leg side, he gets beaten in the flight and makes contact with the inner part of the bat. The bat turned on impact as well. The ball flies in the air at Mahmudullah, who takes a simple catch

milestones.description: Shane Watson has broken the record for most sixes in an innings (15) in ODIs for AUS, going past Hayden's 10
Shane Watson has broken the record for most runs in boundaries (150) in an innings in ODIs for AUS, going past Ricky Ponting's 106
Shane Watson's 185 is the highest individual score in ODIs (for AUS), surpassing Hayden's 181
Shane Watson has broken the record for most sixes in an innings (15) in ODIs, going past Marshall's 12
Shane Watson has broken the record for most runs in boundaries (150) in an innings in ODIs, going past Gibbs's 126
